content:
For each 
sector image, once all TJs are located, three EBSP images are obtained for each TJ (in the 3 grains around each TJ); 
these provide the 3D orientation of each grain and fully describe each TJ.

When a GB curves near a TJ and noise occurs near a TJ, its location and its dihedral angle estimates are poor; 
we note new algorithm variations to provide accurate locations and dihedral angle estimates for TJs  (and to 
automatically note when such estimates are expected to be poor).
